Business Problem
Due to the credit system in America, there are many people that find it difficult or impossible to get a loan. Home Credit aims for financial inclusion by providing loan services this
demographic while controlling default risk. 
The aim of this project is to create a default risk model using alternative historical data that maximizes assessment accuracy.

Benefit of a Solution
The results of this project will:
• Increase the number of loan approvals while controlling risk, leading to a larger
customer base.
• Decrease losses due to defaulting, improving profitability.
• Financially empowering more customers.

Analytics Approach
Data Preparation
To clean up the provided data, we handled NAs, factorized character / categorical variables, and removed variables that did not have a significant impact on the target variable.
We selected the top variables with higher predictive power to remove noise from the dataset and enhance model performance.
We also utlized feature engineering to boost the model's AUC.

Key Findings
The most important features that we found (in order of significance) were: EXT_SOURCE_MED, EXT_SOURCE_2 & 3, RATIO_AMT_ANNUITY_TO_AMT_CREDIT, RATIO_AMT_CREDIT_TO_AMT_ANNUITY, AMT_ANNUITY, DAYS_EMPLOYED, AMT_GOODS_PRICE.

Modelling
We created logistic regression, random forest, and boosted tree models and compared their performance based on AUC.
With these models, we performed a grid search method to choose the best hyperparameter settings.
Our top performing model was our boosted tree model, with an AUC of 754.

