Individual Contribution
Each of us created our own EDA files and models and compared the model performances.
I tinkered with the random forest and random forest models for our final model selections.

Business Value
The final model delivers the following business benefits:
- The model has a 91.5% classification accuracy with AUC of 0.754.
- The model identifies high risk customers that will help the company reduce defaults.
- This will in turn reduce losses from defaults while maximizing approved loans from reliable customers.

Challenges:
One thing that we struggled with that we could improve upon is the use of alternative datasets to include into the model to fit the company's mission of financial inclusion better.
I believe there is more we could've done to be more creative with the feature engineering to boost the AUC further.

Tech Stack Used:
- Language: R
- Libraries: tidymodels, tidyverse, caret, pROC, grf, lightgbm, xgboost,bonsai, vip.
- Modelling Approach: Tidymodels workflow with cross-validation and hyperparameter turning.
- Validation: 5-fold cross-validation on 80/20 train-test split.
